value.value: 膵臓β細胞の欠如
absence of the cells of the pancreas that secrete insulin
膵臓β細胞の分化異常

atypical production of or inability to produce the cells that secrete insulin and are located towards the center of the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas, and/or accumulation of pancreatic beta cell precursors
膵臓α細胞数の増加
increase in the number of the cells of the pancreas that secrete glucagon
膵臓α細胞数の減少
reduction in the number of the cells of the pancreas that secrete glucagon
膵臓α細胞の欠如
absence of the cells of the pancreas that secrete glucagon
膵臓α細胞の分化異常
atypical production of or inability to produce the cells of the pancreas that secrete glucagon, and/or accumulation of pancreatic alpha cell precursors
膵臓δ細胞数の増加
increased number of the cells found in the pancreas that secrete somatostatin
膵臓δ細胞数の減少
reduced number of the cells found in the pancreas that secrete somatostatin
膵臓δ細胞の欠如
absence of the cells found in the pancreas that secrete somatostatin
膵臓δ細胞の分化異常
atypical production of or inability to produce the cells found in the pancreas that secrete somatostatin, and/or accumulation of pancreatic delta cell precursors
PP細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the polygonal pancreatic polypeptide producing cells in the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas
PP細胞数の増加
increased number of the polygonal pancreatic polypeptide producing cells in the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas
PP細胞数の減少
reduced number of the polygonal pancreatic polypeptide producing cells in the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas
PP細胞の欠如
absence of the polygonal pancreatic polypeptide producing cells in the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas
PP細胞の分化異常
atypical production of or inability to produce the polygonal pancreatic polypeptide producing cells in the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas, and/or accumulation of PP cell precursors
膵臓ε細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the endocrine cells found in the Islets of Langerhans that produce the hormone ghrelin
膵臓ε細胞数の増加
increase in the number of the endocrine cells found in the Islets of Langerhans that produce the hormone ghrelin
膵臓ε細胞数の減少
reduction in the number of the endocrine cells found in the Islets of Langerhans that produce the hormone ghrelin
膵臓ε細胞の欠如
absence of the endocrine cells found in the Islets of Langerhans that produce the hormone ghrelin
膵臓ε細胞の分化異常
atypical production of or inability to produce the endocrine cells found in the Islets of Langerhans that produce the hormone ghrelin, and/or accumulation of pancreatic epsilon cell precursors
膵臓ε細胞の生理異常
any functional anomaly of the endocrine cells found in the Islets of Langerhans that produce the hormone ghrelin
PP細胞の生理異常
any functional anomaly of the polygonal pancreatic polypeptide producing cells in the islets of Langerhans in the pancreas
膵臓のグレリン分泌異常

anomaly in the production and/or regulated release from pancreatic epsilon cells of a 28-amino acid, acylated, orexigenic peptide that acts centrally to stimulate growth hormone secretion and food intake, and peripherally to regulate energy homeostasis; it is cleaved from a large precursor protein, known as appetite-regulating hormone or motilin-related peptide, which contains both ghrelin and obestatin

definition.value: Ghrelin-secreting cells are found mainly in the stomach and duodenum, but also in the jejunum, lungs, pancreatic islets, gonads, adrenal cortex, placenta, kidney and brain.

value.value: 膵臓のポリペプチド分泌異常

anomaly in the production and/or regulated release of the 36-amino acid pancreatic hormone that is secreted mainly by endocrine cells found at the periphery of the islets of Langerhans in response to ingestions, and regulates gastric secretion, gastric emptying, pancreatic enzyme secretion, and appetite
雄の生殖器形態異常
any structural anomaly of the masculine organs of reproduction or generation, external or internal
雄の外生殖器形態異常
any structural anomaly of the external masculine genital organs, including the penis and scrotum
雄の外生殖器肥大
increased size of the external masculine genital organs, including the penis and scrotum
雄の外生殖器萎縮

acquired diminution of the size of the external masculine genital organs, associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes
雄の外生殖器矮小化
reduced size of the external masculine genital organs
雄の外生殖器形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the external male genitalia, typically resulting in decreased size
雄の外生殖器欠如
absence of the external masculine genital organs, including the penis and scrotum
雄の内生殖器形態異常
any structural anomaly of the internal masculine genital organs, including the testes, epididymides, deferent ducts, seminal vesicles, prostate, ejaculatory ducts, and bulbourethral glands
雄の内生殖器欠如
absence of the internal masculine genital organs, including the testes, epididymides, deferent ducts, seminal vesicles, prostate, ejaculatory ducts, and bulbourethral glands
雄の内生殖器形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the internal male genitalia, typically resulting in decreased size
雌の生殖器形態異常
any structural anomaly of the feminine organs of reproduction or generation, external or internal
雌の内生殖器形態異常
any structural anomaly of the internal feminine genital organs, including the ovaries, uterine tubes, uterus, uterine cervix, and vagina
雌の内生殖器欠如
absence of the internal feminine genital organs, including the ovaries, uterine tubes, uterus, uterine cervix, and vagina
雌の外生殖器欠如
absence of the external feminine genital organs, collectively known as the vulva
外陰部萎縮

acquired diminution of the size of the external feminine genital organs, collectively known as the vulva, associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes
雄の鼠径管欠如
absence of the passage in the lower abdominal wall through which the spermatic cord, nerves and vessels normally pass from the pelvic cavity to the scrotum
輸精管形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the vas deferens, typically resulting in decreased size
子宮角欠如
absence of either one of the pair of tubular extensions from the uterine body where the uterus and the uterine tubes meet
腹膜形態異常

any structural anomaly of the serous sac, consisting of mesothelium and a thin external layer of irregular connective tissue, that lines the abdominopelvic cavity and covers most of the viscera contained therein; it forms two sacs: the peritoneal (or greater) sac and the omental bursa (lesser sac) connected by the omental foramen
腹膜鞘状突起形態異常

any structural anomaly of the peritoneal diverticulum in the embryonic lower anterior abdominal wall that traverses the inguinal canal; in the male it forms the tunica vaginalis testis and normally loses its connection with the peritoneal cavity; a persistent processus vaginalis in the female is known as the canal of Nuck
腹膜鞘状突起欠如
absence of the peritoneal diverticulum in the embryonic lower anterior abdominal wall that traverses the inguinal canal
前立腺上皮内新生物
higher than normal incidence of a non-invasive neoplastic proliferation of the epithelial cells that line the acini and the ducts of the prostate gland
前立腺癌発生率上昇
higher than normal incidence of a malignant neoplasm arising from prostate tissue
子宮腺筋症
a benign invasion of myometrium by endometrial tissue
子宮腫瘍発生率上昇
greater than the expected number of abnormal rapidly proliferating cells in the uterus, usually in the form of a distinct mass, occurring in a specific population in a given time period
子宮癌の発生率増加
greater than the expected number of malignant neoplasms derived from uterine epithelial cells, occurring in a specific population in a given time period
